    <h2 class="useCaseHeading">Guidelines for Using the Academic Resource Portal</h2>
<div class="How-to-use">
    <div class="step">
        <span>Step 1 – Select Academic Details</span>
        Select your branch, semester, academic year, and examination type (Mid-Semester or End-Semester) to
        access the relevant previous year question papers.
    </div>
    <div class="step">
        <span>Step 2 – Review Previous Examination Patterns</span>
        Review multiple previous year question papers to identify recurring topics, mark distribution,
        and commonly asked question formats.
    </div>
    <div class="step">
        <span>Step 3 – Prepare for Examinations Systematically</span>
        Use the question papers to revise concepts, practice answer writing within time limits, and prioritize frequently tested topics for effective preparation.
    </div>
